## Task 7 Hashing for Integrity Checking

File integrity: hashing verifies files haven’t been altered.
Example: compare SHA256 checksum of downloaded ISO with official checksum.
Duplicate detection: identical hashes = identical files.
HMACs: Keyed-Hash Message Authentication Codes.
Combine hash function + secret key.
Provide authenticity (sender identity) + integrity (message unchanged).
Formula:
𝐻𝑀𝐴𝐶(𝐾,𝑀)=𝐻((𝐾⊕𝑜𝑝𝑎𝑑) ∣∣ 𝐻((𝐾⊕𝑖𝑝𝑎𝑑) ∣∣ 𝑀))

